emotes.msg: There is nothing more I can do with this.
Heh, I bet I can sell this for quite a bit!  What's that, you want it back?  Bah...
How disgusting!
There is, however, a sage somewhere in the southern mountain range that actually likes those things.  How revolting...
Hmm, I think that might fit on the Niffis Helm.
Are you telling me to dress better?  I don't need your charity!
Small hides are only provide enough material for bracers.
Here you go.
Oh, this should make a very nice breastplate.
Here you go.
There really is a lot of armoredillo hide here. I should be able to make a coat from this.
Here you go.
This hide is very sturdy. I can line this with silk for a fine piece of armor.
Here you go.
Here you go!
Here you go!
Here you go!
Here you go!
Here you go!
Here you go!
Here you go!
Here you go!
Here you go!
I can make a good set of greaves from these.
Here you go.
Reedshark hides make good leggings.
Here you go.
I'll make a pair of mattekar hide sleeves from this. Should help keep you warm.
Here you go.
You look like you want a dependable mattekar hide coat. This should be a good fit.
Here you go.
Wow, this thing reminds me of those strange Hoary Mattekar hides.  Only, not as hoary, or protective, for that matter.  But there is more material here to work with...
Hrm, this is nice!  To bad that you can't act as a sheathe for your dagger.  I saw a guy do that once...
This is a quality piece of work!  With some head gear, you could almost pretend to be a Mattekar!

What an unusual hide. It's a good thing you didn't hand this to me last week. I was making coats out of these hides when I could have been making full robes! Well, you learn something new every day right?
People really seem to prefer these robes over the coats. No wonder, I bet they are far more protective against the elements.
You want this let out so it can be worn as an over-robe too?
It's been a popular change these days.
There, you should be able to get armor on with it now.
Those small shreths are useless, don't you think?  Good thing they drop skins, otherwise no one would kill them.
Shreths are foul creatures.  But you can make comfortable shoes out of them, so I guess they aren't all bad.
Heh, there is nothing like getting a good shank of hide out of some stupid unsuspecting animal.  There's enough here to make some pants.  Here you go.
Ursuin are smelly creatures that always seem to have enough life left in them to almost fall on you when you kill them.  This is enough hide to cover your midriff.  Here you go.
Ursuin coats are almost like Mattekar coats, they are just harder to get, because Mattekars are weak.
Hmm, this looks like a spring hide!  Well, it seems the Ursuin are starting to really adapt to our climate, eh?
Hmm.  These Spring coats are thinner than the winter ones, but it looks like they give better protection.  I bet it's softer on yer skin too!
Check out the overbite on this sucker!  I bet I can make a pretty decent mace out of this...
Wow, this is a prime piece!  I can make a headpiece out of this one that will protect you and keep your ears warm!
Some days you get the rug.  Other days the rug gets you.
Today, you get the rug!
Wow, this is nice!  Real Sclavus skin is hard to get you know, because there are so many imitations.  Wear these, and make me proud!
This is a nice piece!  You must have gotten it from a pretty large Sclavus.  This will make a pretty nice coat.
With a cut like this, I can make an armored head piece.  It will be so nice, that commanders everywhere will want to wear it!
It is so rare to see such large pieces of Niffis shell!  I'll make this into a functional and stylish shield for you.
This shell must have come from a Niffis.  Tough beasts, they are.  Allow me to make it into a helmet for you.
Ah, a Wisp heart!  This is great!  I can make something that is fairly useful out of this, if you are a mage, that is.
Ah a Pulsating Wisp heart!  These are very powerful.  I can make a very strong orb out of this.
Where did you get this?  I need to go camp there and hunt for these!
This is large enough to craft into a well fitting cuirass I think.
Well then. I think that this may be the first of a great many new robes to come my friend. Make sure to show your friends.
Not quite as sturdy as the tanned red hide that I worked with before, but it's still strong enough and large enough to craft into a nice robe. Wear it well.
Let's see. The hide is thick and leathery, and aside from the small bony protrusions it's in fine shape. I think a nice set of leggings.
There you go.
Another fine specimen. A little thicker than the last shreth hide I was given to work with. Let me have a moment and I'll... Yes, yes that's it!
Here you go.
Where did you get this? It's rather frightening, and rancid smelling. Well, let me see what I can do with it.
Here you go.
I've seen something like this recently. Came from a carenzi though, it mottled and smelled rank. Much like this. Where are you finding these creatures?
Well, I've done the best I can.
What is this!? I've never seen anything like this. It will make a fine robe I think. Give me a moment.
Yes, there it is done.
I've seen some interesting hides pass my way, but the hides that people have been bringing me most recently are the oddest.
A few more threads...and done!
Be careful out there.

Hello, my name's Gillian!  Do you know of any good places to hunt creatures?  I'm looking for standard leather crafter items, plus some wisp hearts, if you find them. Also, if you bring me the hide of an Ursuin Slasher I can make you a comfy Ursuin hide rug.
Did you know that some creatures change along with the seasons?  It makes for prime hunting all year round!
It seems like Dereth is going downhill pretty rapidly.  That's why I'm up here in the Bandit Castle.  After its all over, we'll pick up the pieces.
